<ROOT><RepresentativeData><RepresentativeInfo><PhotoLink>https://images.house.mo.gov/MemberPhoto.aspx?id=2371</PhotoLink><LastName>Oehlerking</LastName><FirstName>Philip</FirstName><DistrictNum>100</DistrictNum><Party>Republican</Party><YearElected>2022</YearElected><YearsServed>3</YearsServed><Hometown>Ballwin</Hometown><Counties><County><CountyName>St. Louis</CountyName></County></Counties><Committees><Committee><CommitteeName>Financial Institutions</CommitteeName><CommitteePosition>Vice-Chair</CommitteePosition></Committee><Committee><CommitteeName>Special Committee on Intergovernmental Affairs</CommitteeName><CommitteePosition>Vice-Chair</CommitteePosition></Committee><Committee><CommitteeName>Rules - Administrative</CommitteeName><CommitteePosition>Member</CommitteePosition></Committee><Committee><CommitteeName>Utilities</CommitteeName><CommitteePosition>Member</CommitteePosition></Committee></Committees><CapitolAddress>MO House of Representatives, 201 West Capitol Avenue, Room 314, Jefferson City MO 65101</CapitolAddress><LegislativeAssistant>Sydney Ryals</LegislativeAssistant><PhoneNumber>573-751-9765</PhoneNumber><EmailAddress>Philip.Oehlerking@house.mo.gov</EmailAddress><Biography>Representative Philip Oehlerking, a Republican, represents part of St. Louis County (District 100) in the Missouri House of Representatives. He was elected to his first two-year term in November 2022.

Prior to his service in the legislature, Oehlerking worked at the Missouri Higher Education Loan Authority (MOHELA). He also spent two years working for the Show-Me Institute.  

A graduate of the University of Missouri – St. Louis, Oehlerking received his bachelor’s degree in Political Science in 2015.

Oehlerking resides in Ballwin with his wife and daughter, and he has an active role as deacon at Trinity Presbyterian Church.
